I returned to Chicago after a 30-year absence in July, 2020. Since then I have eaten in only 2 restaurants, La Creperie and Francis on Clark. I did not realize at the time that I would be unable to go again anytime soon because of the shutdown, but I am still delighted by my choices. La Reperie was a longtime favorite, and in spite of no longer being able to eat what I used to (I skipped the wine because I no longer drink, and I could not manage to finish my swiss and mushroom favorite savory crepe - I took half home -so I could not manage my favorite chocolate banana dessert) It was still glorious to eat a crepe I could never equal in New York.
Amazing food, great service.   Extremely friendly and attentive when needed.  Have been back a few times and excellent every time!

If there is a cozier restaurant in Chicago, I don't know where it is. La Creperie is an old style, homey, French spot with good food and a nice wine selection. It's also right across the street from a pretty 'arsty' movie theater. Creperie plus a movie, makes for a perfect date night. Highly recommend!

I only give 5 stars because I can't give more.  My husband and I discovered this place when we were dating. We came here to eat before a major state exam I had to take and the staff was great as well as the food. We would come back every year aftee that as an anniversary for passing my test that day. (We don't live close, if not we would probably be there at least once a week) My husband proposed to me here, we came when I was pregnant, and now our son has also enjoy this place.  ❤❤❤❤❤

A little understaffed, so service was a little slow. But they had just reopened during the covid crisis, so that was entirely forgivable. We had brunch. The crepes were scrumptious. Egg dish was also excellent. It's a cute place and we were touched by the personal greeting by a gentleman we presumed to be the owner. Highly recommended!

A Chicago crepe institution! They're following all the safety precautions for covid-19, and over two decades I've always had perfect crepes there. Vegetarians have options there as well! Highly recommend the spinach crême. Save room for dessert!

Hidden back patio is great at night, I believe is not well known, otherwise it would be full. Nice ambient, not crowded, you can reserve by phone and the food is nice if you are into crepes. Service was great, they allowed us to stay chatting long after the rest of customers.

It was truly magical. Our server, Allen, was delightful and so sweet! He allowed me to try different wines until we selected the perfect dry champagne to have with our escargot!! I can't believe I had escargot! Sadly, they didn't have any vegan options, so this was an ethical cheat day for me. We sat in the back and there was a candle on each table and little lights strung up and they were so magical. I did not pay, I am sure it was pricey, but honestly, from the food, to the service, to the overall mood of the setting, it was a priceless evening dinner. Thank you, Allen!
A Chicago staple. I hope they are doing well during these times. If you can please support them, we will be back asap!

Delish! I absolutely loved the chicken curry crepe. So unusual and unique. I wouldn’t order the croque madame again—the bread wasn’t good, so it was basically an overblown ham and cheese sandwich. Maybe go for the ham and Swiss crepe instead! Also I saw someone get the cheese board, and it was pretty underwhelming. 3 chunks of cheese, room temperature bread, and a few slices of apple. But I’d love to try the escargot! Will definitely be back—I didn’t even get a chance to try any of the sweet crepes! Also there’s a hidden back patio that is so pleasant.
I loved it

This is a surprisingly hidden gem. La Crêperie is a charming restaurant with wonderful food for incredibly reasonable prices and a wonderful wine selection. The rustic decor puts one at ease despite what could be an intimidating amount of French on the menu -- don't worry the descriptions are in English. The staff is amazing, the service often feels more like a conversation with a friend than a transactional interaction. Both the savory and sweet crêpes are delicious, additionally you can't go wrong with their French onion soup which becomes my winter staple. The menu caters both to people who might want to try something unfamiliar and to those with more traditional tastes. The restaurant is always busy, but I've never seen it too busy to get a table even with larger groups. La Crêperie is a delightful Chicago spot that should be added to everyone's list of go-to favorites.
We had our office party here. They were great. There dessert crepes were absolutely fantastic. The staff worked with us to make the whole thing come off. Can't wait to go back.

The French onion soup was also the worst anyone at our table had ever had, mostly due to a very strange strong herb in the soup that we couldn't identify and should not be in any French onion soup. I should have realized something was up when the waiter brought the cold soup and put it down in front of me, but I assumed he had an attitude of “ladies first” as he heard our plans to share and well, cold soup come out faster than hot, right? Imagine my dismay when the next time a server approached our table was to bring the crepes - no soup for me :( by the time I realized it definitely was forgotten, it was too late to order. I’m not entirely sure why I never received what I ordered, but it left me with a bad taste in my mouth.

La Crêperie French Restaurant still maintains its original French Crêpes Suzettes menu since 1972, on Clark Street across the Century Shopping Center.  For the last 46 years, La Crêperie has a loyal following of gourmet and gourmand francophiles who enjoy a quiet ambiance, wonderful service, and a French sense of food.  Since I was a high school student studying French with my former teacher Pat D'Andrea, I was invited to visit La Crêperie with our Catholic High School's French Club.  La Crêperie retains its French American local charm in the Windy City and still serves authentic Crêpes Suzettes.  Bon appétit!

What a wonderful French Creperie! We enjoyed the savory crepe that was salted with the right type of flour...our choice was the poulet champignons (chicken with creamy sauce and mushrooms). It was delicious, the crepe was generously stuffed with meat and mushrooms....too much for my stomach! I had to abandon after eating the half...since we were at the hotel, I could not take the left over with me, but I regret because it was very good! The French rose wine was excellent and again this glass of wine was served generously...For dessert, we shared a huge sweet crepe "Suzette a la Germain" (grand marnier flambe & orange with lemon reduction), Erick did a formidable thing for us who are used in France to eat flambee= crepe suzette....he served it at our table using a match to burn the grand marnier on the top!!! Staff was so friendly and made us feeling happy, having a delightful dinner. Thank you again Erick and to all your team.

Really enjoyed the escargot.  I like the croque monsiuer, although I think out had too much cheese.  Shared a Carmel crepe for dessert that was really good.  I have head many other great meals here, before.  The onion soup is always good.  The atmosphere a me service assets reliable.
Delicious!!!
You can’t get a more authentic French Crepe restaurant in this city. The outdoor patio in the summer is probably the cutest space there is! Perfect for dates.
Delicious food, place looks truly authentic
One of my favorite brunch places. Very cool French aesthetic for any francophile as well
Mostly yum!
This place has the best crepes in the city. It's small and cozy but the food is phenomenal!
Dined here 3 times.  Always fantastic.  Delicious food at reasonable prices combined with excellent service.  Looking forward to a return visit soon.
My favorite brunch spot in Chicago.  Glad we made it up there on this trip.

Lovely and intimate restaurant with delicious crepes.  I really love the warm and intimate feeling of this place.  It was like being in a small french bar with people that I really love and also the food is damn good.  Decently priced and with generous portions.  Usually crepes seem to be somewhat flimsy or light.  But La Creperie Chicago offers desserts that have more heft.  They also have savory crepes and an apparently notable/famous french onion soup, but I've yet to try them.  Hopefully soon because I'm going again!
Cozy and delicious. Great post-movie spot - especially with the free crêpe with movie stub offer. Nice cocktail, beer, and wine list too.
The service and food is great.

Great service! Everyone was very nice and helpful. The crepes are top notch. Some of the best French onion soup I’ve had. I do wish the coconut chocolate crepe had a little less coconut. But that’s my only bit on constructive criticism. Great spot!
Good customer service and food was delicious
My favorite in Chicago! Great atmosphere especially in the summer garden, great wine, and while crepes rule - escargot are a must for me!
Cozy. Authentic

Overall: Great crepes and great atmosphere, will definitely be coming back here at some point!  The good: Great crepes with a lot to choose from, either sweet or savory. The prices are pretty reasonable as well, and the crepes are quick large. The atmosphere is great, with a rustic feeling. Great music as well. Very intimate but not intimidating.  The bad: The service, while friendly, wasn't the best. We were almost charged for more food than we got, the waiter also didn't understand the amount of our food or the request to have the dessert crepe to come out after our savory crepes.  Atmosphere: 9/10 Service: 7.5/10 Food: 9/10

Wonderful little place in Lakeview with some French staples in addition to the wide-array of crepes.  Had the Escargot appetizer and a bowl of French Onion Soup (cheese on top crispy/gooey perfection) straight out of the oven, then split a savory crepe and a sweet one.  This was too much food but the variety was a plus and everything tasted freshly made and authentic. It was surprisingly affordable for the amount of stuff we ordered.  Atmosphere is intimate but casual.  Great date spot.  We went on half-off wine (bottle) night which is Tuesday and made the whole experience feel like quite a bargain.  Service was friendly and professional.  This will be a new go-to for casual dates or when I am craving French Onion soup (always).
The ambience is cozy yet lively, and the food is phenomenal. They have an extensive selection of savory and sweet crepes with a well-curated wine list to match. Would highly recommend!
The salted caramel latte is amazing. Order it with extra foam on top. Favorite crepe is definitely the curry chicken with mango chutney.
A lovely Chicago tradition.

Pretty good place for brunch. I got the complete crepe and it comes with the egg in the inside. I think tho that I would prefer the crepe and egg and bacon separately since the crepe stays crunchier that way.  there is a good amount of butter in the crepe- makes it delish! And I would get mimosas here. They are light and not too heavy on the booze. They also have cocktail specials that are seasonal. They open about 11 for brunch so if you come by 1130 there usually isn't a wait
yummy and adorable
Always a joy to eat at La Creperie! Great french food, plus you can get a free dessert with your dinner if you have a ticket stub from the Landmark Cinema across the street.
Paté and French onion soup for lunch?  Yes please!
Great, unique (to Chicago) food, and the patio has a real St. Bart's vibe. Perfect for rose and post-colonial ennui.
I used to go to La Creperie in the 1980's And it is better than ever today.

Disappointing. Hubs had a previous great experience. His order was taken wrong and the "chef's alternative" to what they thought he'd ordered (not even close) but were out of some ingredients, was a heavy plate of mushy stuff. The remade crepe was okay. Niçoise salad just had toppings sparsely dumped on top of roughly chopped lettuce. No finesse or thought to balance of ingredients. It was a shame, as everyone said it was amazing.
Favorite place for a crepe. Coffee is very good. Edit: Over a year later and still our favorite place to go for a bite and a super cup of coffee.
The crepes are delicious focusing only on the food, the decor is old, cozy Chicago restaurant and in the winter they turn on the fire place.
Great crapes!!

The food was good, but the prices were a little high for what we got. Great crepes but nothing on the side for around 15 to 20 a crepe. We sat in the back patio and that could be the reason, but service was only occasionally checking on us. Overall this place was good, but we probably won't be back without an occasion.
Food was wonderful! Nice small and homey, good wine, great service!

We had a late lunch here.  The service was excellent and there's a beautiful garden to eat in out back.  My son got a Nutella crepe and my husband and I got an apple crepe to share.  The crepes were beautiful presented and reasonably priced.  The one we got to share was brought out on two plates which made things easier.  Would definitely recommend.
Very good crepes at reasonable prices!
This place was classy and served great food. The wine list was long and the crepes were delicious. They had both sweet and savory.

Unchanged, after all! We ate there when they reopened, and it was a disappointment. However, we went back a year later and I'm happy to report that they're back on track. Lunch was classic French bistro, and it was like reconnecting with an old friend.

This place has good crepe choices. Beside their sweet menu they have some French sandwiches as well. We tried their coconut and nutella crepe which was delucious and their croq. Their drinks have high quality as well. Besides the food their design is very unique. They can work on their service a little bit, but over all it is a must go place for brunch.
Great menu, atmosphere and service - not to be missed!

Chicken and mushroom was :D
Best Crepes in Chicago!!
Seafood crepe, pate plate, sauternes.
Amazing Nutella crepes. Add vanilla ice cream on top for the best dessert you have ever had! Very nice staff.

I'm worried to be too honest with my review but we absolutely love this place. It's probably our favorite place in our neighborhood.  Even if it was totally crowded, we still come wait to eat here... but the one of the bonuses of this place is that it's a hidden gem, hence my reservations with gushing over this place.  Although I'd love it to remain a quaint little reclusive spot, I also want the business to enjoy all the attention it deserves.  Bottom line: (1) great food, including sweet and savory crepes (and an amazing croque madam) and ice cream locally made right up the street at Bobtail, (2) three different dining areas (front, back, and garden/patio) all with a unique and French vibe, (3) great service, (4) a full bar with a solid wine list, and (5) all at great prices.  The place works well for a quick dine in meal with friends and fam, or for a more serious date night.  The menu easily accommodates breakfast, lunch, and dinner.  Bon appetit!
Best French onion soup I'd ever had. Try the salted caramel crepe with peanut-butter inside. Been coming here for years.

They have a lovely outdoor space that is well covered from the sun. Croque madame was delicious while the same ingredients in the crepe were just OK. Next time I will try a sweet crepe as the savory was too dense.
